    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 125, bookName: "Zephaniah", chapter: 3, verse: 17, text: "The LORD thy God in the midst of thee is mighty; he will save, he will rejoice over thee with joy; he will rest in his love, he will joy over thee with singing."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 126, bookName: "Matthew", chapter: 5, verse: 14, text: "Ye are the light of the world. A city that is set on an hill cannot be hid."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 127, bookName: "Matthew", chapter: 5, verse: 16, text: "Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father which is in heaven."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 128, bookName: "Matthew", chapter: 7, verse: 7, text: "Ask, and it shall be given you; seek, and ye shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you:"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 129, bookName: "Matthew", chapter: 7, verse: 12, text: "Therefore all things whatsoever ye would that men should do to you, do ye even so to them: for this is the law and the prophets."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 130, bookName: "Luke", chapter: 12, verse: 7, text: "But even the very hairs of your head are all numbered. Fear not therefore: ye are of more value than many sparrows."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 131, bookName: "John", chapter: 10, verse: 11, text: "I am the good shepherd: the good shepherd giveth his life for the sheep."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 132, bookName: "John", chapter: 10, verse: 14, text: "I am the good shepherd, and know my sheep, and am known of mine."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 133, bookName: "John", chapter: 10, verse: 28, text: "And I give unto them eternal life; and they shall never perish, neither shall any man pluck them out of my hand."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 134, bookName: "John", chapter: 16, verse: 33, text: "These things I have spoken unto you, that in me ye might have peace. In the world ye shall have tribulation: but be of good cheer; I have overcome the world."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 135, bookName: "Acts", chapter: 4, verse: 12, text: "Neither is there salvation in any other: for there is none other name under heaven given among men, whereby we must be saved."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 136, bookName: "Acts", chapter: 16, verse: 31, text: "And they said, Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ, and thou shalt be saved, and thy house."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 137, bookName: "Romans", chapter: 8, verse: 1, text: "There is therefore now no condemnation to them which are in Christ Jesus, who walk not after the flesh, but after the Spirit."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 138, bookName: "Romans", chapter: 8, verse: 38, text: "For I am persuaded, that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principalities, nor powers, nor things present, nor things to come,"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 139, bookName: "Romans", chapter: 8, verse: 39, text: "Nor height, nor depth, nor any other creature, shall be able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ Jesus our Lord."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 140, bookName: "1 Corinthians", chapter: 10, verse: 13, text: "There hath no temptation taken you but such as is common to man: but God is faithful, who will not suffer you to be tempted above that ye are able; but will with the temptation also make a way to escape, that ye may be able to bear it."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 141, bookName: "2 Corinthians", chapter: 4, verse: 17, text: "For our light affliction, which is but for a moment, worketh for us a far more exceeding and eternal weight of glory;"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 142, bookName: "2 Corinthians", chapter: 4, verse: 18, text: "While we look not at the things which are seen, but at the things which are not seen: for the things which are seen are temporal; but the things which are not seen are eternal."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 143, bookName: "Ephesians", chapter: 6, verse: 10, text: "Finally, my brethren, be strong in the Lord, and in the power of his might."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 144, bookName: "Ephesians", chapter: 6, verse: 11, text: "Put on the whole armour of God, that ye may be able to stand against the wiles of the devil."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 145, bookName: "Philippians", chapter: 1, verse: 6, text: "Being confident of this very thing, that he which hath begun a good work in you will perform it until the day of Jesus Christ:"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 146, bookName: "Colossians", chapter: 2, verse: 6, text: "As ye have therefore received Christ Jesus the Lord, so walk ye in him:"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 147, bookName: "Colossians", chapter: 3, verse: 1, text: "If ye then be risen with Christ, seek those things which are above, where Christ sitteth on the right hand of God."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 148, bookName: "1 Thessalonians", chapter: 4, verse: 17, text: "Then we which are alive and remain shall be caught up together with them in the clouds, to meet the Lord in the air: and so shall we ever be with the Lord."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 149, bookName: "1 Timothy", chapter: 6, verse: 6, text: "But godliness with contentment is great gain."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 150, bookName: "1 Timothy", chapter: 6, verse: 12, text: "Fight the good fight of faith, lay hold on eternal life, whereunto thou art also called, and hast professed a good profession before many witnesses."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 151, bookName: "Titus", chapter: 3, verse: 5, text: "Not by works of righteousness which we have done, but according to his mercy he saved us, by the washing of regeneration, and renewing of the Holy Ghost;"),
    // ── June: Psalms ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 152, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 16, verse: 11, text: "Thou wilt shew me the path of life: in thy presence is fulness of joy; at thy right hand there are pleasures for evermore."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 153, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 19, verse: 1, text: "The heavens declare the glory of God; and the firmament sheweth his handywork."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 154, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 19, verse: 14, text: "Let the words of my mouth, and the meditation of my heart, be acceptable in thy sight, O LORD, my strength, and my redeemer."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 155, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 23, verse: 2, text: "He maketh me to lie down in green pastures: he leadeth me beside the still waters."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 156, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 23, verse: 3, text: "He restoreth my soul: he leadeth me in the paths of righteousness for his name's sake."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 157, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 23, verse: 4, text: "Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil: for thou art with me; thy rod and thy staff they comfort me."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 158, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 23, verse: 6, text: "Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life: and I will dwell in the house of the LORD for ever."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 159, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 27, verse: 14, text: "Wait on the LORD: be of good courage, and he shall strengthen thine heart: wait, I say, on the LORD."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 160, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 29, verse: 11, text: "The LORD will give strength unto his people; the LORD will bless his people with peace."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 161, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 30, verse: 5, text: "For his anger endureth but a moment; in his favour is life: weeping may endure for a night, but joy cometh in the morning."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 162, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 31, verse: 3, text: "For thou art my rock and my fortress; therefore for thy name's sake lead me, and guide me."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 163, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 32, verse: 7, text: "Thou art my hiding place; thou shalt preserve me from trouble; thou shalt compass me about with songs of deliverance. Selah."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 164, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 34, verse: 1, text: "I will bless the LORD at all times: his praise shall continually be in my mouth."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 165, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 34, verse: 8, text: "O taste and see that the LORD is good: blessed is the man that trusteth in him."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 166, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 34, verse: 18, text: "The LORD is nigh unto them that are of a broken heart; and saveth such as be of a contrite spirit."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 167, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 37, verse: 4, text: "Delight thyself also in the LORD: and he shall give thee the desires of thine heart."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 168, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 37, verse: 5, text: "Commit thy way unto the LORD; trust also in him; and he shall bring it to pass."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 169, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 40, verse: 1, text: "I waited patiently for the LORD; and he inclined unto me, and heard my cry."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 170, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 40, verse: 2, text: "He brought me up also out of an horrible pit, out of the miry clay, and set my feet upon a rock, and established my goings."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 171, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 42, verse: 1, text: "As the hart panteth after the water brooks, so panteth my soul after thee, O God."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 172, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 46, verse: 10, text: "Be still, and know that I am God: I will be exalted among the heathen, I will be exalted in the earth."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 173, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 51, verse: 10, text: "Create in me a clean heart, O God; and renew a right spirit within me."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 174, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 55, verse: 22, text: "Cast thy burden upon the LORD, and he shall sustain thee: he shall never suffer the righteous to be moved."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 175, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 56, verse: 3, text: "What time I am afraid, I will trust in thee."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 176, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 62, verse: 8, text: "Trust in him at all times; ye people, pour out your heart before him: God is a refuge for us. Selah."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 177, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 63, verse: 1, text: "O God, thou art my God; early will I seek thee: my soul thirsteth for thee, my flesh longeth for thee in a dry and thirsty land, where no water is;"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 178, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 68, verse: 19, text: "Blessed be the Lord, who daily loadeth us with benefits, even the God of our salvation. Selah."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 179, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 71, verse: 5, text: "For thou art my hope, O Lord GOD: thou art my trust from my youth."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 180, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 73, verse: 26, text: "My flesh and my heart faileth: but God is the strength of my heart, and my portion for ever."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 181, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 84, verse: 11, text: "For the LORD God is a sun and shield: the LORD will give grace and glory: no good thing will he withhold from them that walk uprightly."),
    // ── July: More Psalms / Trust ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 182, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 86, verse: 15, text: "But thou, O Lord, art a God full of compassion, and gracious, longsuffering, and plenteous in mercy and truth."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 183, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 90, verse: 2, text: "Before the mountains were brought forth, or ever thou hadst formed the earth and the world, even from everlasting to everlasting, thou art God."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 184, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 91, verse: 1, text: "He that dwelleth in the secret place of the most High shall abide under the shadow of the Almighty."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 185, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 91, verse: 2, text: "I will say of the LORD, He is my refuge and my fortress: my God; in him will I trust."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 186, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 91, verse: 4, text: "He shall cover thee with his feathers, and under his wings shalt thou trust: his truth shall be thy shield and buckler."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 187, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 91, verse: 11, text: "For he shall give his angels charge over thee, to keep thee in all thy ways."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 188, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 94, verse: 19, text: "In the multitude of my thoughts within me thy comforts delight my soul."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 189, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 100, verse: 1, text: "Make a joyful noise unto the LORD, all ye lands."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 190, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 100, verse: 3, text: "Know ye that the LORD he is God: it is he that hath made us, and not we ourselves; we are his people, and the sheep of his pasture."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 191, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 100, verse: 5, text: "For the LORD is good; his mercy is everlasting; and his truth endureth to all generations."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 192, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 103, verse: 1, text: "Bless the LORD, O my soul: and all that is within me, bless his holy name."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 193, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 103, verse: 3, text: "Who forgiveth all thine iniquities; who healeth all thy diseases;"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 194, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 103, verse: 13, text: "Like as a father pitieth his children, so the LORD pitieth them that fear him."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 195, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 107, verse: 9, text: "For he satisfieth the longing soul, and filleth the hungry soul with goodness."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 196, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 112, verse: 7, text: "He shall not be afraid of evil tidings: his heart is fixed, trusting in the LORD."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 197, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 116, verse: 1, text: "I love the LORD, because he hath heard my voice and my supplications."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 198, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 118, verse: 24, text: "This is the day which the LORD hath made; we will rejoice and be glad in it."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 199, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 119, verse: 9, text: "Wherewithal shall a young man cleanse his way? by taking heed thereto according to thy word."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 200, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 119, verse: 11, text: "Thy word have I hid in mine heart, that I might not sin against thee."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 201, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 119, verse: 130, text: "The entrance of thy words giveth light; it giveth understanding unto the simple."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 202, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 121, verse: 1, text: "I will lift up mine eyes unto the hills, from whence cometh my help."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 203, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 121, verse: 2, text: "My help cometh from the LORD, which made heaven and earth."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 204, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 121, verse: 7, text: "The LORD shall preserve thee from all evil: he shall preserve thy soul."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 205, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 121, verse: 8, text: "The LORD shall preserve thy going out and thy coming in from this time forth, and even for evermore."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 206, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 127, verse: 1, text: "Except the LORD build the house, they labour in vain that build it: except the LORD keep the city, the watchman waketh but in vain."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 207, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 130, verse: 3, text: "If thou, LORD, shouldest mark iniquities, O Lord, who shall stand?"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 208, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 130, verse: 7, text: "Let Israel hope in the LORD: for with the LORD there is mercy, and with him is plenteous redemption."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 209, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 133, verse: 1, text: "Behold, how good and how pleasant it is for brethren to dwell together in unity!"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 210, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 139, verse: 7, text: "Whither shall I go from thy spirit? or whither shall I flee from thy presence?"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 211, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 139, verse: 16, text: "Thine eyes did see my substance, yet being unperfect; and in thy book all my members were written, which in continuance were fashioned, when as yet there was none of them."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 212, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 143, verse: 10, text: "Teach me to do thy will; for thou art my God: thy spirit is good; lead me into the land of uprightness."),
    // ── August: Proverbs / Wisdom ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 213, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 145, verse: 3, text: "Great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised; and his greatness is unsearchable."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 214, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 145, verse: 18, text: "The LORD is nigh unto all them that call upon him, to all that call upon him in truth."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 215, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 147, verse: 3, text: "He healeth the broken in heart, and bindeth up their wounds."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 216, bookName: "Psalms", chapter: 150, verse: 6, text: "Let every thing that hath breath praise the LORD. Praise ye the LORD."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 217, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 1, verse: 7, text: "The fear of the LORD is the beginning of knowledge: but fools despise wisdom and instruction."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 218, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 2, verse: 6, text: "For the LORD giveth wisdom: out of his mouth cometh knowledge and understanding."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 219, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 3, verse: 7, text: "Be not wise in thine own eyes: fear the LORD, and depart from evil."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 220, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 4, verse: 7, text: "Wisdom is the principal thing; therefore get wisdom: and with all thy getting get understanding."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 221, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 10, verse: 12, text: "Hatred stirreth up strifes: but love covereth all sins."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 222, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 11, verse: 2, text: "When pride cometh, then cometh shame: but with the lowly is wisdom."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 223, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 11, verse: 14, text: "Where no counsel is, the people fall: but in the multitude of counsellors there is safety."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 224, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 12, verse: 1, text: "Whoso loveth instruction loveth knowledge: but he that hateth reproof is brutish."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 225, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 13, verse: 20, text: "He that walketh with wise men shall be wise: but a companion of fools shall be destroyed."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 226, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 14, verse: 12, text: "There is a way which seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 227, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 15, verse: 1, text: "A soft answer turneth away wrath: but grievous words stir up anger."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 228, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 16, verse: 18, text: "Pride goeth before destruction, and an haughty spirit before a fall."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 229, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 17, verse: 22, text: "A merry heart doeth good like a medicine: but a broken spirit drieth the bones."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 230, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 19, verse: 11, text: "The discretion of a man deferreth his anger; and it is his glory to pass over a transgression."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 231, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 21, verse: 21, text: "He that followeth after righteousness and mercy findeth life, righteousness, and honour."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 232, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 23, verse: 26, text: "My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my ways."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 233, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 24, verse: 16, text: "For a just man falleth seven times, and riseth up again: but the wicked shall fall into mischief."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 234, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 25, verse: 11, text: "A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in pictures of silver."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 235, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 27, verse: 1, text: "Boast not thyself of to morrow; for thou knowest not what a day may bring forth."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 236, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 28, verse: 1, text: "The wicked flee when no man pursueth: but the righteous are bold as a lion."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 237, bookName: "Proverbs", chapter: 29, verse: 25, text: "The fear of man bringeth a snare: but whoso putteth his trust in the LORD shall be safe."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 238, bookName: "Ecclesiastes", chapter: 12, verse: 13, text: "Let us hear the conclusion of the whole matter: Fear God, and keep his commandments: for this is the whole duty of man."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 239, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 1, verse: 18, text: "Come now, and let us reason together, saith the LORD: though your sins be as scarlet, they shall be as white as snow; though they be red like crimson, they shall be as wool."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 240, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 6, verse: 8, text: "Also I heard the voice of the Lord, saying, Whom shall I send, and who will go for us? Then said I, Here am I; send me."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 241, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 9, verse: 2, text: "The people that walked in darkness have seen a great light: they that dwell in the land of the shadow of death, upon them hath the light shined."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 242, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 26, verse: 3, text: "Thou wilt keep him in perfect peace, whose mind is stayed on thee: because he trusteth in thee."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 243, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 40, verse: 28, text: "Hast thou not known? hast thou not heard, that the everlasting God, the LORD, the Creator of the ends of the earth, fainteth not, neither is weary? there is no searching of his understanding."),
    // ── September: OT Prophets ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 244, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 40, verse: 29, text: "He giveth power to the faint; and to them that have no might he increaseth strength."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 245, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 43, verse: 1, text: "But now thus saith the LORD that created thee, O Jacob, and he that formed thee, O Israel, Fear not: for I have redeemed thee, I have called thee by thy name; thou art mine."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 246, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 43, verse: 2, text: "When thou passest through the waters, I will be with thee; and through the rivers, they shall not overflow thee: when thou walkest through the fire, thou shalt not be burned; neither shall the flame kindle upon thee."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 247, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 44, verse: 6, text: "Thus saith the LORD the King of Israel, and his redeemer the LORD of hosts; I am the first, and I am the last; and beside me there is no God."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 248, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 45, verse: 22, text: "Look unto me, and be ye saved, all the ends of the earth: for I am God, and there is none else."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 249, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 48, verse: 17, text: "Thus saith the LORD, thy Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel; I am the LORD thy God which teacheth thee to profit, which leadeth thee by the way that thou shouldest go."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 250, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 54, verse: 10, text: "For the mountains shall depart, and the hills be removed; but my kindness shall not depart from thee, neither shall the covenant of my peace be removed, saith the LORD that hath mercy on thee."),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 251, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 55, verse: 6, text: "Seek ye the LORD while he may be found, call ye upon him while he is near:"),
    VerseOfTheDayEntry(dayOfYear: 252, bookName: "Isaiah", chapter: 55, verse: 8, text: "For my thoughts are not your thoughts, neither are your ways my ways, saith the LORD."),
